== '''Noun''' ==

'''depredation'''

1. An act of consuming agricultural resources (crops, livestock), especially as plunder. 

2. (usually plural ''depredations'') Ravages.

"Union Gen. William Tecumseh Sherman had long known that his fragile supply and communication lines through Tennessee were in serious jeopardy because of ''depredations'' by Forrest's cavalry raids." (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Brice%27s_Crossroads)